ext":"The classic presentation includes difficulty opening the mouth, which progresses over time.","dimension":10,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051662,0.094934,0.093815,0.09237,0.093267,0.095148,0.092814,0.09074,0.082203,0.08074,0.069191,0.063116],"unified_progress":[0.053464,0.080183,0.085829,0.089617,0.092206,0.098764,0.094414,0.095183,0.089911,0.085866,0.074011,0.060551]},{"section":12,"text":"Since she's been using tobacco for so long, that timeline fits.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046418,0.085653,0.091583,0.093699,0.095118,0.10197,0.092736,0.090776,0.084693,0.084644,0.072034,0.060674],"unified_progress":[0.08796,0.11502,0.097644,0.093167,0.087059,0.087949,0.081976,0.086262,0.076598,0.072808,0.062687,0.050871]},{"section":13,"text":"Other possibilities might include infections like tetanus, but she doesn't have other symptoms like muscle spasms or a history of injury.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031434,0.067988,0.078705,0.085403,0.091114,0.096327,0.10191,0.1029,0.098587,0.094985,0.087371,0.063282],"unified_progress":[0.040618,0.070662,0.08151,0.087803,0.097328,0.097796,0.098952,0.10102,0.097799,0.09623,0.078778,0.051499]},{"section":14,"text":"Temporomandibular joint disorders can cause trismus too, but usually there's a history of trauma or clicking sounds, which aren't mentioned here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026476,0.060855,0.07353,0.083099,0.090317,0.096332,0.10372,0.10525,0.10339,0.099884,0.090542,0.066604],"unified_progress":[0.03281,0.060454,0.075807,0.084426,0.094587,0.099501,0.10193,0.10604,0.10439,0.10509,0.08354,0.051417]},{"section":15,"text":"Also, the absence of ulcers might rule out conditions like oral candidiasis or aphthous ulcers, which can sometimes cause pain and limit movement, but she has no ulcers.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026092,0.059448,0.071637,0.081194,0.088909,0.095493,0.10326,0.10547,0.10378,0.10173,0.092862,0.070124],"unified_progress":[0.030606,0.057666,0.072379,0.081601,0.091985,0.098083,0.10154,0.10653,0.10589,0.10854,0.08812,0.057057]},{"section":16,"text":"Oral submucous fibrosis is known to be associated with areca nut chewing, which is common in tobacco products in some regions.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032679,0.064495,0.075274,0.087176,0.096537,0.10236,0.10323,0.10015,0.093845,0.094424,0.079882,0.069945],"unified_progress":[0.051407,0.069893,0.080317,0.088062,0.09307,0.10262,0.10013,0.099944,0.094567,0.08885,0.074117,0.057015]},{"section":17,"text":"The fibrosis leads to contracture of the buccal mucosa and the muscles involved in opening the mouth.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036987,0.076366,0.084711,0.091336,0.094296,0.097956,0.098395,0.094001,0.098724,0.084763,0.074592,0.067873],"unified_progress":[0.046837,0.072073,0.087947,0.096693,0.10188,0.10198,0.098494,0.09489,0.096212,0.0794,0.067211,0.056379]},{"section":18,"text":"The lack of ulcers might be because the fibrosis is more advanced, or maybe the ulcers have healed and now it's the scarring that's causing the problem.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035679,0.072923,0.082443,0.089177,0.093196,0.096594,0.098423,0.096082,0.095547,0.089169,0.080453,0.070314],"unified_progress":[0.045906,0.066828,0.079593,0.088537,0.095636,0.096932,0.097702,0.096976,0.096569,0.090345,0.079384,0.065592]},{"section":19,"text":"Another thought: maybe a tumor?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025573,0.060446,0.079896,0.089582,0.096571,0.096808,0.099618,0.10094,0.099151,0.098565,0.08655,0.0663],"unified_progress":[0.031758,0.068965,0.087161,0.10166,0.10138,0.098607,0.10324,0.098705,0.09403,0.091589,0.072755,0.050154]},{"section":20,"text":"But the gradual onset over years and the association with tobacco use points more towards a chronic fibrotic process rather than a neoplasm.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024597,0.05847,0.074522,0.084242,0.09113,0.095353,0.10055,0.10143,0.10097,0.099684,0.092211,0.076839],"unified_progress":[0.034836,0.063575,0.076904,0.086725,0.093947,0.096648,0.098842,0.10136,0.099317,0.098905,0.084786,0.064158]},{"section":21,"text":"Also, tumors would likely present with a mass or other symptoms.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.01661,0.046259,0.063029,0.075284,0.085012,0.0933,0.10625,0.11182,0.11295,0.11161,0.10524,0.07263],"unified_progress":[0.025045,0.051297,0.067893,0.077067,0.091365,0.094654,0.10188,0.11075,0.11123,0.11892,0.094626,0.05528]},{"section":22,"text":"So putting it all together, the chronic tobacco use leading to fibrosis of the oral mucosa, resulting in trismus without current ulcers, makes oral submucous fibrosis the most likely diagnosis here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026217,0.052149,0.061542,0.06938,0.075768,0.081815,0.087721,0.091479,0.097705,0.10067,0.10675,0.1488],"unified_progress":[0.029474,0.040551,0.050063,0.060553,0.066504,0.075753,0.082032,0.08836,0.095632,0.10266,0.13192,0.17649]}]}}